I recently created a new advertiser account and submitted three ad campaigns. However, all of them have been stuck in "Pending" status for over 36 hours. I understand that the review process may take some time, but I wanted to check if there’s any issue with my account or the ads themselves.

Could you please look into this for me or let me know if any action is required on my end?

Hi there! I understand your concern about the pending status of your ad campaigns. If your account is new and hasn't been verified yet, this could be causing the delay. To proceed with the verification process, please provide the following details by emailing adsupport@newsbreak.com with the subject line: Business Verification –
- Company's full address
- Company's legal entity name
- Company's EHID or DUNS number
- Primary contact person's name
- Company's phone number
Once we receive this information, we will conduct a thorough review and update you on your account status. We appreciate your cooperation in maintaining a secure and compliant advertising environment for all our partners.

Thank you for the instructions.

I have sent the requested business verification information to adsupport@newsbreak.com as advised. Please let me know if anything else is needed from my side.

Looking forward to your confirmation.

You're welcome! Thank you for sending the business verification information. Our team will review the details and get back to you as soon as possible. If we need any additional information, we will reach out to you. In the meantime, if you have any other questions or need further assistance, feel free to let me know!
